ReviewText: if you re searching for this you know what it is my gas range is the standard 36 range with built in oven that is found in many homes nothing fancy the problem is that there is small gap between the range and the cabinet countertop that food or liquid can fall into these stainless steel stove gap covers solves exactly this problem due to its proximity to the fire and heat the gap cover must be metal and because will be exposed to oils and other food particles it needs to be easy to clean these covers fit both criteria with an extendable piece these covers can fit all ranges regardless of the depth of the stove and there is small metal piece that is supposed to provide tension when inserted into the gap unfortunately this is where have the first problem with this product the tension just isn enough to keep the gap cover in the gap snugly think cork or silicone piece would help give it the friction in needs to stay in place the second problem have is that the product is in the shape of the letter but because there is slight difference in height between my range and the counter it has to tilt to one side further making it hard for the cover to stay in place the last issue is the extension part it doesn lock into position without it you can accidentally push on the cover and shorten it it would be better to have some sort of locking mechanism that will keep it to the length that you set this product does what its intended for but think few tweaks and it would be perfect might just look to see if can make these tweaks myself

ReviewText: great little pour over filter with some problems drink pour over coffee almost exclusively and wanted to get away from the disposable filters this looked just like what needed so got it it has lot of good features super easy to use and clean and it looks nice too and doesn take up too much space the screen is very fine so no coffee grounds got through the screen is so fine yet works so well that suspect could even use this on rooibos tea which is very fine indeed on to the problems the silicone rubber ring around the base was half off when it came out of the package couldn get it back on it doesn really matter in terms of operation but kind of not good idea to have something breaking right out of the package also don get why the coffee scoop has brush on the end of it for cleaning the screen guess but it seems odd to me to have it on the end of the coffee scoop and frankly it didn help with cleaning it all but the mesh did just rinse clean don really see this thing lasting that long finally as others have noted it makes fairly weak cup of coffee have another cup filter like this that doesn start filtering until you put it on the cup which means you can let it brew longer much prefer that filter to this one although that one uses disposable filters there may be trick to learning to do good pour over so perhaps my complaints reflect that but for now think ll keep using my other filter with the new reusable linen filters found on amazon might use this to filter tea after ve steeped it in pot it is great fine mesh filter but overall this doesn quite suit my needs

ReviewText: had to return it for replacement but the replacement unit is pretty good needed to replace my old 19 cf refrigerator and needed that size again because of the space in my kitchen and there are only 3 models sold with bottom draw freezer in that size kenmore maytag and whirlpool based on pictures they all look the same but consumer reports rated kenmore highest and it was also least expensive so this is the one decided on bought it on amazon because it had quicker delivery than directly from sears and same price but included free hookup including ice maker and free haul away of the old unit first the negatives needed left hand door and the refrigerator typically is set up right hand but designed for easy change in the distribution center before delivery it was really hard to figure out how to specify left hand door with the amazon order ultimately had to call 3 times to get someone to confirm it would be done left hand second when it was delivered the door had been damaged when the handle position was moved initially agreed to have kenmore send the parts to replace the door but then thought better of it and accepted amazon offer to replace the whole refrigerator have decided not to post the photos here of the damage it was delivered with since ultimately they made it right third while waiting for the replacement unit the refrigerator started making grinding crackling sound coming from the back of the unit not inside that clearly indicated something important was wrong didn explore further since we were getting replacement anyway both amazon and kenmore were very responsive re customer service and cannot say enough positive about the people one at each place who helped make things right but still it was pain regarding the refrigerator itself it works well and keeps food cold ice maker is working great so far for small refrigerator like this having the pull out drawer on the bottom is really great compared to my older unit which was ge but they no longer make this size it has much larger freezer space but much smaller refrigerator space the larger freezer space is nice but much prefer the larger refrigerator to freezer space this is really small refrigerator unit finally the temperature controller and light is at the top front of the refrigerator compartment so it blocks moving things in and out easily its surprisingly bad design that makes small space even less usable but from what can see all 3 of the brands available are identical in the refrigerator freezer space ratio and in placement of the thermostat light so if 19 cf bottom freezer is what you want that is all that available the exterior design is ok there are 2 plastic plugs on the outside of the door that are pretty unsightly its really cheesy design to cover the holes for swapping the handle there are 2 crispers with adjustable humidity and meat deli drawer they are nice to have but pretty cheap quality plastic although seems to me that is standard the door shelves are ok although there is some wasted space in the design but again think all the brands available in this size with bottom freezer drawer are identical

second when it was delivered the door had been damaged when the handle position was moved
third while waiting for the replacement unit the refrigerator started making grinding crackling sound coming from the back of the unit not inside that clearly indicated something important was wrong

ReviewText: first of all we are limited by the nominal 12 volt power in vehicle this heater draws about 10 amperes but that depends on the actual vehicle voltage my vehicle will idle at about 14 5 volts so it is able to put more power into the heater so it boils water slightly faster when the product description says glass or ceramic container they mean it if you try to use metal container the metal will radiate and waste heat if you try to use something silly like foam plastic it will likely melt plus you want to choose the container volume carefully if you use large volume container the heater coil will not sink down into the cold water far enough so the whole thing will burn up and fail we are trying to get some volume around 8 ounces to boil if you try it with 6 ounces of cold water it will boil relatively quickly found that could get good results about 8 minutes to boil using 7 ounces of water in glass ceramic mug and the heater coil sticks down into the cold water ymmv if your vehicle battery is different and if you have the heater plugged into socket that is long way from the battery over poor choice of wire then the power to the heater will be lower just don make the mistake of letting the heater flip off of the mug lip then it will be out of the water it will burn up and fail so choose your pieces and parts carefully

ReviewText: it worked decently at first but after several months it can no longer produce ice at this point its just eating up electricity to turn water into slightly colder water huge waste of money edit 5 5 22 they worked with me and provided full refund for the order they even provided way to troubleshoot the machine but unfortunately already threw it out by then good customer service

ReviewText: i recently purchased keurig and had lot of coffee left from my old drip brew machine purchased the eco fill pods in order to use up that coffee they are accomplishing that but will not continue using them after the coffee is gone due to the design the lids do not stay closed during the brewing process sometimes you end up with coffee grounds in the bottom of your cup think they just need better latching mechanism and they will have very useful product
